<br>
The 3 skill points into Improved Natural Regeneration &amp; 3 points into First Aid, would indede be sufficient to start acquiring Melee Archetype Abilities.<br>
<br>
To get class abilities you must spend 12 points in Archetype Abilities.  The minimum number of points you can spend for one level in one Archetype Ability is 2 points, followed by 4 points and then 6 points.  Meaning that it should be impossible to spend 3 points in one Archetype Ability.  You could spend 2 points in 6 abilities, 12 points in one ability, or 6 points in two different abilities.<br>
<br>
When describing points and abilites people need to make a distinction between points spent and levels of abilities gained.  Raven does bring about an interesting point though.  Spreading yourself out a bit more instead of devoting points all into one area may increase ones overall utility more than specializing.<br>
<br>
Personally, im still debating, but I'm thinking of:<br>
point 1: Natural Regen level 1<br>
point 2,3: Natural Regen level 2<br>
point 4,5,6: Natural Regen level 3<br>
point 7,8: Combat Fury level 1<br>
point 9,10: Finishing Blow level 1<br>
point 11,12,13,14: Combat Fury level 2<br>
point 15,16,17,18: Finishing Blow level 2<br>
point 19,20,21,22,23,24: Chaotic Stab<br>
<br>
If it truely takes the roughly the same amount of exp as is required to get through level 51 to gain a skill point, exp wise thats like going from 1st to 59.5th level to gain 24 points. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I hope that the post, where I saw people saying that the same amount of exp to get through 51st would be needed to get one skill point, was in error.<br>
